00:05:15.539 --> 00:05:16.080
So let's see.

00:05:16.080 --> 00:05:18.702
We know one side
of this triangle.

00:05:18.702 --> 00:05:20.910
Let's see if we could figure
out this side over here.

00:05:20.910 --> 00:05:22.243
It seems pretty straightforward.

00:05:22.243 --> 00:05:25.880
This is going to be a right
triangle right over here,

00:05:25.880 --> 00:05:28.810
because this line
from D to M is going

00:05:28.810 --> 00:05:30.770
to be perpendicular to AB.

00:05:30.770 --> 00:05:34.650
All of the points that are
equidistant between A and B

00:05:34.650 --> 00:05:40.104
are going to be on a line
that is perpendicular to AB.

00:05:40.104 --> 00:05:41.770
So this is going to
be a right triangle.

00:05:41.770 --> 00:05:46.380
So we can figure out DM using
the Pythagorean theorem again.

00:05:46.380 --> 00:06:00.890
We get 25/2 squared
plus DM squared

00:06:00.890 --> 00:06:03.109
is going to be
equal to 15 squared.

00:06:03.109 --> 00:06:05.400
It's going to equal to the
hypotenuse of this triangle.

00:06:05.400 --> 00:06:09.500
So it's going to equal 225.

00:06:09.500 --> 00:06:10.650
And so what do we get?

00:06:10.650 --> 00:06:20.779
We get DM squared is
equal to 225 minus 625/4.

00:06:20.779 --> 00:06:21.820
So let's put this over 4.

00:06:21.820 --> 00:06:26.960
So 225 with 4 as the denominator
is the same thing as 900/4.

00:06:29.730 --> 00:06:33.800
And in the last video, I
actually mistakenly said 900/4

00:06:33.800 --> 00:06:35.812
was 125, obviously a
boneheaded mistake.

00:06:35.812 --> 00:06:37.270
But the numbers
show up again here.

00:06:37.270 --> 00:06:40.050
So 225 is obviously 900/4.

00:06:40.050 --> 00:06:42.100
And then we're going to
subtract from that 625/4.

00:06:47.930 --> 00:06:50.870
And this is equal
to-- let's see.

00:06:50.870 --> 00:06:54.510
In our numerator, we
have 900 minus 625

00:06:54.510 --> 00:06:55.860
would be 300 minus 20.

00:06:55.860 --> 00:06:56.870
It's going to be 275/4.

00:07:00.670 --> 00:07:05.390
And so DM is going to be equal
to the square root of this.

00:07:05.390 --> 00:07:08.660
So it's equal to the
square root of 275/4.

00:07:08.660 --> 00:07:14.380
275 is 25 times 11, because
25 times 12 would be 300.

00:07:14.380 --> 00:07:17.180
So 25 times 11 over 4.

00:07:17.180 --> 00:07:23.240
So this is going to be equal
to 5 square roots of 11 over 2.

00:07:23.240 --> 00:07:27.220
So DM is 5 square
roots of 11 over 2.

00:07:30.810 --> 00:07:32.560
So what we need to
do here is figure out

00:07:32.560 --> 00:07:34.680
the height of this
triangle right over here.

00:07:34.680 --> 00:07:37.552
If we could figure out the
height of that triangle,

00:07:37.552 --> 00:07:38.510
we're pretty much done.

00:07:38.510 --> 00:07:42.320
1/2 the base times the height,
but we don't know-- let's see,

00:07:42.320 --> 00:07:44.720
we could figure that if we
know the law of cosines.

00:07:44.720 --> 00:07:46.095
We could do
something over there.

00:07:46.095 --> 00:07:50.319
If we know the sine of
this angle right over here,

00:07:50.319 --> 00:07:51.860
the sine of that
angle is going to be

00:07:51.860 --> 00:07:55.820
this height over the
side we just figured out.

00:07:55.820 --> 00:07:58.390
So if we could figure out
the sine of that angle,

00:07:58.390 --> 00:08:01.430
then we'd be done, or we'll
be very close to being done.

00:08:01.430 --> 00:08:03.306
But it's not any obvious way.

00:08:03.306 --> 00:08:05.430
But one thing we can do,
if you look at this bigger

00:08:05.430 --> 00:08:08.120
triangle over here--
so let me highlight it.

00:08:08.120 --> 00:08:10.760
So if you look at triangle BMC.

00:08:10.760 --> 00:08:13.990
Let me draw triangle BMC.

00:08:13.990 --> 00:08:16.342
Well, I'll just draw it on
