00:09:00.780 --> 00:09:04.950
It's going to be our theta that
we care about plus 90 degrees.

00:09:04.950 --> 00:09:10.550
So this angle right here
is theta plus 90 degrees.

00:09:10.550 --> 00:09:12.190
And this over here is 24.

00:09:12.190 --> 00:09:16.630
This is 25/2, and this is 25/2.

00:09:16.630 --> 00:09:18.790
And so using this, we could
use the law of cosines

00:09:18.790 --> 00:09:23.480
to figure out what
theta actually is here.

00:09:23.480 --> 00:09:24.750
So let's do that.

00:09:24.750 --> 00:09:26.875
We're going to use a little
bit of trig identities,

00:09:26.875 --> 00:09:27.960
but law of cosines.

00:09:27.960 --> 00:09:31.190
So we get the opposite
to the angle squared,

00:09:31.190 --> 00:09:33.660
so we get 24 squared.

00:09:33.660 --> 00:09:44.080
24 squared is equal to 25/2
squared, plus 25/2 squared,

00:09:44.080 --> 00:09:54.460
minus 2 times 25/2 times 25/2
times the cosine of this angle,

00:09:54.460 --> 00:09:57.840
times-- let me scroll
over-- the cosine

00:09:57.840 --> 00:10:03.676
of theta plus 90 degrees.

00:10:03.676 --> 00:10:05.300
Now, you're saying,
hey, Sal, you know,

00:10:05.300 --> 00:10:08.340
this has it in terms of cosine
of theta plus 90 degrees.

00:10:08.340 --> 00:10:10.190
How can we figure out
the sine of theta?

00:10:10.190 --> 00:10:11.720
That's what we
actually care about,

00:10:11.720 --> 00:10:13.390
to figure out the
area of this triangle,

00:10:13.390 --> 00:10:16.080
or actually to figure out
the height of this triangle.

00:10:16.080 --> 00:10:19.520
And to do that, you just
have to make the realization.

00:10:19.520 --> 00:10:24.660
We know the trig identity
that the cosine of theta

00:10:24.660 --> 00:10:26.780
is equal-- I won't use
theta because I don't want

00:10:26.780 --> 00:10:34.250
to overload theta-- cosine of x
is equal to sine of 90 minus x.

00:10:34.250 --> 00:10:41.170
So the cosine of
theta plus 90 degrees

00:10:41.170 --> 00:10:44.530
is going to be equal to
the sine of-- let me put it

00:10:44.530 --> 00:10:47.280
in parentheses-- 90
minus whatever is here.

00:10:47.280 --> 00:10:53.070
90 minus theta minus 90,
which is equal to-- the 90's

00:10:53.070 --> 00:10:56.844
cancel out-- sine
of negative theta.

00:10:56.844 --> 00:10:58.260
And we know sine
of negative theta

00:10:58.260 --> 00:11:03.010
is equal to the
negative sine of theta.

00:11:03.010 --> 00:11:05.400
So this over here
simplifies to-- this

00:11:05.400 --> 00:11:06.692
is the negative sine of theta.

00:11:06.692 --> 00:11:08.150
So we could write
the sine of theta

00:11:08.150 --> 00:11:10.990
here and then put the
negative out here.

00:11:10.990 --> 00:11:12.680
And this becomes a positive.

00:11:12.680 --> 00:11:13.930
So what does this simplify to?

00:11:13.930 --> 00:11:18.830
We have 24 squared,
which is 576.

00:11:18.830 --> 00:11:23.260
576 is equal to-- let's see.

00:11:23.260 --> 00:11:24.590
I won't skip any steps here.

00:11:24.590 --> 00:11:27.250
So we have 25 squared
plus 25 squared.

00:11:27.250 --> 00:11:40.620
This is 2 times 25/2
squared plus 2 times--

00:11:40.620 --> 00:11:48.250
this is 25/2 squared
again-- times sine of theta.

00:11:48.250 --> 00:11:51.020
Now we just have to
solve for sine of theta.

00:11:51.020 --> 00:11:53.250
So this is going to
be equal to-- well,

00:11:53.250 --> 00:12:02.210
this is 576 is equal to
2 times 25/2 squared.

00:12:02.210 --> 00:12:03.620
I'm just factoring that out.

00:12:03.620 --> 00:12:05.760
1 plus sine of theta.

00:12:08.870 --> 00:12:12.194
Or we can just divide both sides
of the equation by this here.

00:12:12.194 --> 00:12:13.610
Actually, let me
just simplify it.

00:12:13.610 --> 00:12:17.770
This thing over here is
625/4, but then we're

00:12:17.770 --> 00:12:19.150
going to multiply that by 2.

00:12:19.150 --> 00:12:23.300
So this thing over
here is 625/2.

00:12:23.300 --> 00:12:26.270
So let's divide both
sides of this by 625/2.

00:12:26.270 --> 00:12:35.660
And we get 576
times 2 over 625--

00:12:35.660 --> 00:12:38.230
just multiplying both sides
by the inverse-- is equal to.

00:12:38.230 --> 00:12:40.730
When you multiply both sides
by the inverse [? like this, ?]

00:12:40.730 --> 00:12:46.570
it actually cancels out-- is
equal to 1 plus sine of theta.

00:12:46.570 --> 00:12:49.880
Or we just subtract
1 from both sides.

00:12:49.880 --> 00:12:53.800
We get sine of theta is
equal to 576 times 2.

00:12:53.800 --> 00:12:57.460
Let's see, 76 times
2 is 152, plus 1,000.

00:12:57.460 --> 00:13:02.780
So it's 1,152/625.

00:13:02.780 --> 00:13:05.110
That's that part there, minus 1.

00:13:05.110 --> 00:13:07.750
But instead of 1,
let's say 625/625.

00:13:07.750 --> 00:13:10.650
So minus 625.

00:13:10.650 --> 00:13:14.140
And this is equal to-- I'll
have to do a little math

00:13:14.140 --> 00:13:20.550
on the side-- so
1,152 minus 625.

00:13:20.550 --> 00:13:21.700
You get a 12 there.

00:13:21.700 --> 00:13:22.535
This becomes a 4.

00:13:22.535 --> 00:13:23.970
12 minus 5 is 7.

00:13:23.970 --> 00:13:25.845
4 minus 2 is 2.

00:13:25.845 --> 00:13:27.990
11 minus 6 is 5.

00:13:27.990 --> 00:13:32.451
So this is equal to 527/625.

00:13:32.451 --> 00:13:34.950
Now, you might not realize it,
